Rodong Sinmun on Self-reliant Defense Capacity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- Self-reliant defense capabilities are the best means of defending sovereignty of the country and the nation from the strong arm and arbitrariness of the imperialist aggressor forces, declares  Rodong Sinmun in a signed article Friday, which reads in part:
 The countries and peoples treasuring the dignity of the nation and the sovereignty of the country, small countries in particular, should direct great efforts to increasing defense capabilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The practical experience of the DPRK tells that the sovereignty of the country can be defended and the dignity and honor of the nation be exalted only when importance is attached to military affairs and defense capabilities are augmented.
 The Korean people are proud of the fact that they have bolstered self-reliant defense capacity on the principle of giving priority to military affairs, tightening their belts in the past period. No other country but the DPRK has firmly defended socialism in face of constant high-handed military blackmail and aggressive threat by the U.S. imperialists for decades. The U.S. imperialists would have already attacked the DPRK many a time, if it had not built up colossal self-reliant defense capacity. It was entirely right for the DPRK to have boosted its self-reliant defense capabilities in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  No one can take issue with the DPRK over its defense building for smashing down the moves of the U.S. imperialists to unleash another Korean war and ensuring peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Northeast Asia as it is a legitimate exercise of the right to self-defense. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The peace-loving and progressive people worldwide should fight relentlessly to ensure world peace and security by offering a tough rebuff with military might to the reckless 
military highhandedness of the imperialists.

DPRK to Strongly React to U.S. Moves for War against it with Deterrent for Self-Defence 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- The United States urgently hurled a group of battleships including the nuclear-powered carrier "Enterprise" into south Korea and the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea vociferously cried out for a war of aggression against the DPRK at a time when the U.S. is  escalating its "sanctions" against the DPRK under an absurd pretext.
 In this connection a spokesman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland in a statement issued Friday said: This is an extremely dangerous military provocation intended to drive the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the brink of war.
 The statement went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 South Korea and its vicinity are now crowded with huge U.S. aggressor forces keen to make a military strike at the DPRK and stifle it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Large-scale madcap joint naval and air force maneuvers targeted against the DPRK are now being staged by forces of the U.S. and its allies in the waters of the Pacific and Alaska. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality goes to prove that the U.S. is driving the situation on the peninsula to such a dangerous phase that the second Korean war may break out any moment.
 The army and people of the DPRK will strongly react to the dangerous moves of the U.S. and its allies for a war of aggression against it with its deterrent for self-defence built up under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement strongly demanded the U.S. stop such criminal war moves at once.
 It called upon the south Korean people to heighten vigilance against the prevailing dangerous situation and dynamically turn out in the struggle against the U.S. and war.

DPRK Seriously Affected by Heavy Rains 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- It rained torrentially between 14 and 16 of July, causing heavy human and material losses in many parts of the DPRK.
 The government of the DPRK has taken emergency measures to rehabilitate the disaster-hit areas and investigated the losses. According to the investigation,  several areas in South Phyongan, Kangwon and South Hamgyong Provinces were hit hard.
 In the Yangdok, Sinyang and Songchon areas of South Phyongan Province, a lot of people died, more than 6,200 dwelling houses and some 490 public buildings were partially or totally destroyed and submerged, and thousands of hectares of arable land inundated, washed away and buried. And motor roads, bridges and railway trunk lines were seriously damaged at over 200 points and electricity and communication networks cut off. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 6,000 dwelling houses and over 200 public buildings were partially or totally destroyed and thousands of hectares of farmland were flooded, washed away and buried in Wonsan and various areas of Kangwon Province.
 Similar losses have been reported from Kowon and Yodok areas of South Hamgyong Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of people died or went missing and tens of thousands of houses and public buildings were destroyed partially or totally and submerged beneath water and roads, bridges and railway lines badly damaged at hundreds of points. 
 In particular, the farmland which was havocked in South Hwanghae Province and other rural areas reaches hundreds of thousands of hectares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government is making every effort to recover the affected areas and to stabilize the life of the flood victims.

Railways Talks Held between DPRK and Russia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- Talks between Kim Yong Sam, minister of Railways of the DPRK, and V. I. Yakunin, chairman of the "Russian Railways" Company were held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Friday.
 Present at the talks from the DPRK side were officials concerned and from the Russian side members of the delegation of the "Russian Railways" Company and Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on boosting the bilateral cooperation in the field of railways. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.

DPRK Violinist Highly Acclaimed at International Music Festival
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- Mun Kyong Jin, DPRK winner of international concours, presented his violin solo at the 11th Kaneti International Music Festival, to the high acclaim of the audience.
 The festival is an event to be participated in by winners of the annual Kaneti International Violin Concours, world famous violinists and noted professors.
 The recent festival was held in France on July 14 and 15. Mun was the only violinist to be invited there from among the winners of last year's concours. The festival also drew famous professors and musicians of conservatories and music schools of France, Russia, Germany, Italy and Turkey. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun successfully played musical works of Bach, Paganini and Tchaikovsky requiring high talent for one and half hours in the first day of the festival, winning a high acclaim of the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Prof. Ivanov of Moscow Tchaikovsky State Conservatory said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Promising Korean violinist Mun mesmerized all those present with his high talent. He could emerge a famous violinist in such short period of time under the loving care of leader  Kim Jong Il who brought his talent into bloom and made him known to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appearance of such world famous violinist is the result of the literary and art policy and the policy of training talents pursued by the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Renowned professors of Italy, France and other countries who participated in the festival, sincerely congratulated him, saying in unison that his recital earned him world fame as a violinist of rare gift.    


